---
title: SpacesSync data model (revised after vocab council)
---
flowchart LR
    classDef ui fill:#08427b,stroke:#0a5394,color:#fff,stroke-width:2px
    classDef stored fill:#5a4a1e,stroke:#d4a853,color:#fff,stroke-width:1.5px
    classDef runtime fill:#1168bd,stroke:#0e5aa7,color:#fff,stroke-width:1.5px
    classDef separate fill:#3a2d52,stroke:#7b5fb0,color:#fff,stroke-width:1.5px
    classDef conv fill:#2e7d32,stroke:#4caf50,color:#fff

    subgraph S1 [GUI shape — one row per display]
        UI["position 1 → Group 1<br/>position 2 → Group 1<br/>position 3 → — None<br/>position 4 → Group 2<br/><br/>'Group N' is a derived display label<br/>computed from display order.<br/>Identity is the opaque ID — see S2."]:::ui
    end

    subgraph S2 [Persistent shape — SpacesSync.json]
        JSON["{<br/>  &quot;schemaVersion&quot;: 1,<br/>  &quot;enabled&quot;: true,         ＊master＊<br/>  &quot;syncMode&quot;: &quot;automatic&quot;,  ＊auto or manual＊<br/>  &quot;groupOf&quot;: {<br/>    &quot;1&quot;: &quot;grp_a8x2k0&quot;,<br/>    &quot;2&quot;: &quot;grp_a8x2k0&quot;,<br/>    &quot;4&quot;: &quot;grp_n4f7m1&quot;<br/>  },<br/>  &quot;spaceNames&quot;: {        ＊keyed by group ID＊<br/>    &quot;grp_a8x2k0&quot;: { &quot;1&quot;: &quot;Code&quot;, &quot;2&quot;: &quot;Email&quot; },<br/>    &quot;grp_n4f7m1&quot;: { &quot;1&quot;: &quot;Reference&quot; }<br/>  },<br/>  &quot;_lastSeen&quot;: {        ＊for stale entries＊<br/>    &quot;5&quot;: { name, uuid, date }<br/>  },<br/>  &quot;switchDelay&quot;: 0.3,<br/>  &quot;debounceSeconds&quot;: 0.8,<br/>  &quot;popupDuration&quot;: 2,<br/>  &quot;statusDuration&quot;: 3,<br/>  &quot;hotkeys&quot;: {<br/>    &quot;toggle&quot;:      { mods:[ctrl,alt,cmd], key:&quot;Y&quot; },<br/>    &quot;showNames&quot;:   { mods:[ctrl,alt,cmd], key:&quot;N&quot; },<br/>    &quot;renameSpace&quot;: { mods:[ctrl,alt,cmd], key:&quot;R&quot; },<br/>    &quot;syncNow&quot;:     { mods:[ctrl,alt,cmd], key:&quot;S&quot; },<br/>    &quot;openSettings&quot;:{ mods:[ctrl,alt,cmd], key:&quot;,&quot; }<br/>  }<br/>}"]:::stored
    end

    subgraph S3 [Engine shape — obj.syncGroups]
        ENG["{<br/>  {1, 2},<br/>  {4}<br/>}<br/><br/>Derived from groupOf at runtime.<br/>Stable IDs collapse to ordered<br/>position lists for the sync engine."]:::runtime
    end

    UI -->|same membership<br/>no conversion| JSON
    JSON -->|groupOfToGroups| ENG
    ENG -->|groupsToGroupOf<br/>only on first-run seed| JSON

    Conv1{{"Conversion is one-way at runtime.<br/>JSON is canonical, engine is derived.<br/>list-of-lists never mutated by hand."}}:::conv

    JSON -.- Conv1

    Note1["Single-group constraint is structural.<br/>groupOf is a map keyed by position.<br/>A position has ONE group ID.<br/>Cannot represent overlap by construction."]
    UI -.- Note1

    Note2["Why opaque group IDs?<br/>Letters and numbers reshuffle on changes.<br/>When groups gain metadata in v2<br/>(custom name, color, per-group switchDelay),<br/>label-keyed metadata would follow the wrong<br/>group. Opaque IDs survive every reshuffle.<br/>Group N labels are render-time only."]
    JSON -.- Note2

    Note3["Why is spaceNames in the SAME JSON<br/>keyed by group ID, not split into hs.settings?<br/><br/>Earlier draft kept names in hs.settings keyed<br/>by sorted-position-tuple ('1,2,3'). Reshuffling<br/>groupOf silently stranded names under stale<br/>keys. Group-ID-keyed names in JSON solve this<br/>structurally - reshuffles don't change group IDs,<br/>so names follow membership automatically.<br/><br/>The 'workspace' noun was rejected: names are<br/>just Space names that happen to apply per-group.<br/>No new term needed; the cross-display behavior<br/>is a property of being in a sync group."]
    JSON -.- Note3
